data.description: Exceptional Colonial Revival built in 1920 to accommodate timber baron Frederick Weyerhauser. Located in Cloquet’s West End Historic District, this 9 bed, 7 bath, 6600 sq ft home is superbly and lovingly maintained with modern amenities that don’t sacrifice its original character. Situated on 4.4 acres with a park-like lawn and beautiful perennial gardens, enjoy the solitude and tranquility offered by this property—a delightful surprise for in-town living. Exquisitely designed landscaping welcomes you to the residence, where the large veranda happily hosts visitors before entering the grand foyer. The large but intimate living room with fireplace is to the left, where the formal dining room with antique chandelier is to the right. Relish the sweeping views of the property while savoring dinner with guests. A tastefully updated three-season porch offers a quiet moment for morning coffee or an evening glass of wine. Enjoy the brand- new, meticulously designed custom chef’s kitchen with butler’s pantry, featuring hickory cabinets, quartz countertops, top-of-the-line smart appliances, baking and beverage stations, and more. Additional spaces on the main level include a cozy library with fireplace, wet bar, and large bonus room with laundry. The second level boasts an airy studio/office space, along with six, light-filled bedrooms with ample storage and adjoining bathrooms. The third level includes three bedrooms and an updated bathroom. Exterior features include multiple decks and patios, fenced in areas for pets, a large three-car garage with RV electrical, stunning garden lights, and a whimsical treehouse. Perfect for growing families, multi-gen living, or exploring new business opportunities like the B & B you’ve always dreamed of! On the National Registry of Historic Places with original blueprints, this is a rare chance to own a piece of Cloquet’s history. This magnificent home comes partially furnished with an assumable 2.99% interest rate and is ready for you to move right in!
